title.narrative: The Government multi-sectoral nutrition information system is strengthened for knowledge generation and evidence based decisionmaking

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the President&39;s Office, Regional Administration, and Local Government Tanzania (PORALG) to integrate government-owned data from different sectors into the integrated Monitoring and Evaluation System (iMES). Tanzania Food and Nutrition Center (TFNC) rolled out the Multisectoral Nutrition Information (MNIS) Platform at the national level. The Platform has been cascaded to the district level in all 26 regions on the mainland, timely informing decisions, planning, and accountability in nutrition programming for women, children, and adolescents at all levels. All district councils produced a nutrition scorecard meeting the 2021 target of 100 percent to inform nutrition programming. | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
